body:
Carol Danvers/Daisy Johnson parallels

Being badasses way before getting their superpowers

Getting their powers after exposure to Kree technology (Lightspeed Engine and Terrigen Crystal)

Getting Kree blood pumped into their bodies

Both were captured by the Kree (Yon Rogg and Kasius) and used as a weapon

They both rock a leather jacket 

Projects their powers by their hands

Both can take on an army with their powers alone

Carol and Daisy had a Kree device inhibiting their powers

Both ladies broke free of their Kree mental prison by sheer force of will alone

There is certainly a parallel in Carol’s fight with Yon Rogg and Daisy’s fight with Talbot

did I miss anything?

summary: yesterday i was looking into the dc/marvel amalgam comics, which are comic series from the 90s that dc and marvel did together...
body: yesterday i was looking into the dc/marvel amalgam comics, which are comic series from the 90s that dc and marvel did together where the characters were each a combination of a marvel and a dc character. some of them were just simply a combination of with their corresponding hero, like Aquaman and Sub-Mariner to make Aqua-Mariner. One’s that I found hilarious was marvel’s Captain Marvel and dc’s Captain Marvel (aka Shazam) together and Bruce Wayne and Nick Fury to make Colonel Bruce Wayne

Lottern:A popular term that the swing subculture
used to define itself, roughly translated as something
between "laziness" and "sleaziness", indicating contempt for the
pressure to do "useful work" and the repressive sexual mores of the
time.
---------------
"When the poets only read poetry, the historians only read history, the theorists only read theory, and the philosophers only read philosophy, we experience a clear deficiency in poetry, history, theory, and philosophy. We are far away from Renaissance human beings sculpting themselves to be full and all encompassing in knowledge and life pursuits." - Anthony Leskov
